    {
      "node_id": "engzee_qrs_segmentation",
      "parent_id": "engzee_segmenter_root",
      "name": "engzee_qrs_segmentation",
      "description": "Detects and segments QRS complexes from a raw ECG signal using the Engelse & Zeelenberg algorithm, applying a threshold-based decision rule on the transformed signal to locate R-peak positions and extract beat boundaries.",
      "concept_type": "signal_filter",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "name": "signal",
          "type_desc": "1-D array of ECG amplitude samples",
          "constraints": "must be a uniformly sampled real-valued sequence",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "sampling_rate",
          "type_desc": "positive integer (Hz)",
          "constraints": "must be > 0",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        },
        {
          "name": "threshold",
          "type_desc": "positive float",
          "constraints": "detection sensitivity threshold; must be > 0",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "rpeaks",
          "type_desc": "1-D integer array of sample indices",
          "constraints": "indices into the input signal where R-peaks are detected; sorted ascending",
          "required": true,
          "default_value_repr": ""
        }
      ],
      "status": "decomposed",
      "children": [
        "compute_timing_parameters",
        "differentiate_signal",
        "low_pass_filter_transform",
        "initialise_adaptive_thresholds",
        "update_adaptive_thresholds",
        "find_threshold_crossing",
        "detect_rpeak_in_window",
        "deduplicate_and_sort_rpeaks"
      ],
      "depth": 1,
      "type_signature": "(signal: 1-D array of ECG amplitude samples, sampling_rate: positive integer (Hz), threshold: positive float) -> 1-D integer array of sample indices",
      "matched_primitive": null,
      "primitive_binding_confidence": 0.0,
      "primitive_binding_source": "",
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "threshold_gated_extrema_locator_in_transformed_1d_sequence. Applies a domain-specific differential/nonlinear transform to a uniformly sampled scalar time-series to amplify a target morphological feature (sharp, high-energy transients) while suppressing background variation, then sweeps a scalar threshold across the transformed signal to emit a sorted set of integer indices marking local maxima that exceed the detection boundary. The result partitions the original sequence into contiguous segments whose boundaries are anchored at the detected extremal events, converting a continuous amplitude stream into a discrete event sequence.. Applications: Seismology — detecting P-wave and S-wave onset indices in a continuous ground-motion acceleration time-series recorded at a fixed sampling rate, segmenting the stream into inter-arrival intervals for earthquake localisation, Neurophysiology — locating action potential spike peaks in a extracellular multi-unit electrode voltage trace, partitioning the recording into inter-spike intervals for neural firing-rate estimation, Mechanical fault detection — identifying high-amplitude impulse events in a vibration sensor time-series from a rotating machine bearing, segmenting the signal into cycles to compute defect repetition frequency, Astrophysics / radio astronomy — pinpointing pulse arrival times of periodic transient emitters (e.g., pulsars) in a de-dispersed time-domain intensity series, converting a continuous flux recording into a discrete sequence of pulse-epoch indices for timing analysis",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
    },
